==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gunters quadrant
<hw>Gun"ter's quad`rant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A thin quadrant, made of
brass, wood, etc., showing a stereographic projection on the plane of
the equator. By it are found the hour of the day, the sun's azimuth, the
altitude of objects in degrees, etc. See <er>Gunter's
scale</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gunter's scale</ent>⟦br⟧
